#!/bin/bash - complete setup script run before CODESYS starts:
1. Check if /opt/codesys/bin/codesyscontrol exists; if not, print instructions to run install-codesys-runtime.sh and exit 0 (graceful - don't fail)
2. Set ulimits for current process: memlock unlimited, stack 8MB, nofile 65536
3. Create log directory /var/log/codesys
4. Ensure /var/opt/codesys dirs exist
5. Copy /etc/CODESYSControl.cfg to /var/opt/codesys/cfg/ if not exists there
6. Set CPU3 affinity for this setup process: taskset -cp 3 $$
7. Log readiness

